There's a big TV, a sleek marble bathroom, a small closet, and a large desk in the room.	The room was OK, typical hotel room with queen bed, desk, TV, clock radio, coffee maker.	It'll cost you $3.50, they don't bring sugar or cream, and you can get the same bag of tea in the little coffee maker kit in the bathroom for free.	The rooms were very well decorated, with a flat screen tv, marble bathroom, great view, etc.	We had some issues with hot water and the in-room hairdryer was small and weak (not a big deal, but most hotels now provide the full-size kind).